The paper deals with models for distributed learning, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The communication constraints and limited ability to communicate among agents suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the use of learning agents and fusion centers suggests that the paper may be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the mention of sensor networks suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
